{
  "texts": [
    "When people detect synthetic content, overconfidence could render people susceptible to manipulation.",
    "If individuals are confident in their ability to spot a deepfake but cannot, they may inadvertently engage with manipulated content.",
    "Moreover, analytic thinking and political interest are related in a positive way to correctly detecting deepfakes and are associated with the ability to discriminate fake news negatively [40].",
    "People with high cognitive levels [21] interacting with people's cognitive biases on deepfake might exacerbate distrust in news and information disseminated by public figures [11, 41].",
    "In essence, trust constitutes an alternative decision-making mode, arising from willingly exposing oneself to vulnerability, acknowledging the inherent risk of betrayal, and giving precedence to someone's words over other forms of information [13]."
  ]
}